CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 24, 1954, pg. 12 reads: "Easter Parade - The beautiful weather Sunday drew thousands of devout church-goers to their respective edifices to worship. And it also draw a glamorous parade of charming maids and matrons, bedecked in Easter finery.  Teenie Harris and Oceania Sockwell covered some fifteen churches to get the above photos...No. 5: Daisy L. Porter, Robert L. Porter and Mrs. Nellie Briggs were camera snapped on Centre Avenue by Teenie Harris."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of Daisy L. Porter, Robert L. Porter, and Nellie Briggs, standing in front of Wesley Center A.M.E. Zion Church on Easter Sunday, Centre Avenue
